import numpy as np
import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature
from scipy.stats import ttest_1samp
import geopandas as gpd

# ============================================================
# USER-CONTROL PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
GRID_SIZE      = 2.0
LAT_RANGE      = (5, 40)
LON_RANGE      = (60, 105)

GENESIS_LAT_MAX = 25
TRACK_LEN_MIN   = 12
SPEED_MIN_MS    = 2.0
Q_RECORD_MIN    = 5.0
MIN_SAMPLES     = 30
SIG_LEVEL       = 0.1

DENSITY_MODE    = "mean"
DATA_FILE       = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
N_YEARS         = 2019 - 1998 + 1

QUIVER_SHOW_ONLY_SIGNIFICANT = True
QUIVER_REF_MS     = 2.0
QUIVER_REF_INCH   = 0.2
QUIVER_SCALE_UNITS = "inches"
QUIVER_SCALE      = QUIVER_REF_MS / QUIVER_REF_INCH
QUIVER_WIDTH      = 0.003
QUIVER_HEADWIDTH  = 4
QUIVER_KEY_POS    = (0.86, )
QUIVER_KEY_LABELPOS = 'E'

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)

track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values
lat_rec = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
q_rec   = ds["Q_RECORD"].values

# Define grid
lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
H_unique = np.zeros((lat_bins.size - 1, lon_bins.size - 1), dtype=int)

U_list = [[[] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[1])] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[0])]
V_list = [[[] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[1])] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[0])]

# ============================================================
# Helper: haversine distance
# ============================================================
def haversine(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
    R = 6371.0
    lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2 = map(np.radians, [lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2])
    dlat = lat2 - lat1
    dlon = lon2 - lon1
    a = np.sin(dlat/2)**2 + np.cos(lat1)*np.cos(lat2)*np.sin(dlon/2)**2
    return R * 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(a))

valid_ids = []
dt = 6 * 3600  # 6 hours in seconds

for i in range(track_lengths.shape[0]):
    tl = int(track_lengths[i])
    if tl < TRACK_LEN_MIN:
        continue

    lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
    lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
    if not (np.isfinite(lats[0]) and np.isfinite(lons[0])):
        continue
    if lats[0] >= GENESIS_LAT_MAX:
        continue

    # Mean system speed
    dist_km = np.nansum(haversine(lats[:-1], lons[:-1], lats[1:], lons[1:]))
    hours = max(tl - 1, 1) * 6
    mean_speed_ms = (dist_km * 1000) / (hours * 3600)
    if mean_speed_ms < SPEED_MIN_MS:
        continue

    # Rainy systems filter
    if np.nanmax(q_rec[i, :tl]) <= Q_RECORD_MIN:
        continue

    # Unique-visit density
    li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins) - 1
    lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins) - 1
    mask = (li >= 0) & (li < H_unique.shape[0]) & (lj >= 0) & (lj < H_unique.shape[1])
    visited = set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask]))
    for (ii, jj) in visited:
        H_unique[ii, jj] += 1

    # Stepwise velocities
    for k in range(tl - 1):
        if not (np.isfinite(lats[k]) and np.isfinite(lons[k]) and
                np.isfinite(lats[k+1]) and np.isfinite(lons[k+1])):
            continue

        ii = np.digitize(lats[k], lat_bins) - 1
        jj = np.digitize(lons[k], lon_bins) - 1
        if (ii < 0) or (ii >= H_unique.shape[0]) or (jj < 0) or (jj >= H_unique.shape[1]):
            continue

        dlat = lats[k+1] - lats[k]
        dlon = lons[k+1] - lons[k]
        mean_lat_rad = np.radians((lats[k] + lats[k+1]) / 2.0)

        dy_m = dlat * 111e3
        dx_m = dlon * 111e3 * np.cos(mean_lat_rad)

        u = dx_m / dt
        v = dy_m / dt

        U_list[ii][jj].append(u)
        V_list[ii][jj].append(v)

    valid_ids.append(i)

print(f"Counted {len(valid_ids)} systems after filters.")

# ============================================================
# Density field
# ============================================================
if DENSITY_MODE.lower() == "mean":
    H_plot = H_unique / N_YEARS
    cbar_label = "Mean unique-system density (#/yr per grid cell)"
    title_mode = "Mean Density per Year"
else:
    H_plot = H_unique
    cbar_label = "Unique-system density (total # per grid cell)"
    title_mode = "Total Density (1998–2019)"

# ============================================================
# Mean vectors + significance
# ============================================================
U_mean = np.full_like(H_unique, np.nan, dtype=float)
V_mean = np.full_like(H_unique, np.nan, dtype=float)
mask_sig = np.zeros_like(H_unique, dtype=bool)

for ii in range(H_unique.shape[0]):
    for jj in range(H_unique.shape[1]):
        u_vals = np.asarray(U_list[ii][jj], dtype=float)
        v_vals = np.asarray(V_list[ii][jj], dtype=float)
        if u_vals.size < MIN_SAMPLES:
            continue

        t_u, p_u = ttest_1samp(u_vals, 0.0, nan_policy="omit")
        t_v, p_v = ttest_1samp(v_vals, 0.0, nan_policy="omit")

        if QUIVER_SHOW_ONLY_SIGNIFICANT:
            if (p_u < SIG_LEVEL) or (p_v < SIG_LEVEL):
                U_mean[ii, jj] = np.nanmean(u_vals)
                V_mean[ii, jj] = np.nanmean(v_vals)
                mask_sig[ii, jj] = True
        else:
            U_mean[ii, jj] = np.nanmean(u_vals)
            V_mean[ii, jj] = np.nanmean(v_vals)
            mask_sig[ii, jj] = True

lon_centers = (lon_bins[:-1] + lon_bins[1:]) / 2
lat_centers = (lat_bins[:-1] + lat_bins[1:]) / 2
LONc, LATc = np.meshgrid(lon_centers, lat_centers)

mag = np.sqrt(np.nan_to_num(U_mean)**2 + np.nan_to_num(V_mean)**2)
print(f"Vector speed (m/s): min={np.nanmin(mag):.2f}, max={np.nanmax(mag):.2f}")
# ============================================================
# Plot
# ============================================================
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]], crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())

# --- Ocean background ---
ax.add_feature(cfeature.NaturalEarthFeature(
    "physical", "ocean", "10m",
    facecolor="blue", edgecolor="black"
), zorder=0)

# --- Land background ---
ax.add_feature(cfeature.NaturalEarthFeature(
    "physical", "land", "10m",
    facecolor="lightyellow", edgecolor="black"
), zorder=1)

# --- Coastlines & borders ---
ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE.with_scale("10m"), linewidth=5, zorder=2)
ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS.with_scale("10m"), linestyle=":", linewidth=0.6, zorder=2)

# --- India shapefile overlays ---
country = gpd.read_file(
    "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/india-shapefile/India_Country_Boundary.shp"
).to_crs(epsg=4326)
states = gpd.read_file(
    "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/india-shapefile/India_State_Boundary.shp"
).to_crs(epsg=4326)

# Draw only outlines (transparent inside, so background remains visible)
country.boundary.plot(ax=ax, edgecolor="black", linewidth=1.4, zorder=3)
states.boundary.plot(ax=ax, edgecolor="gray", linewidth=0.6, zorder=3)
# --- Density field ---
LON, LAT = np.meshgrid(lon_bins, lat_bins)
m = ax.pcolormesh(
    LON, LAT, H_plot,
    cmap="Reds",
    shading="auto",
    alpha=0.9,          # <<< transparency so land/ocean is visible
    zorder=2
)
cb = plt.colorbar(m, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)
cb.set_label(cbar_label)

# --- Quiver field (only significant vectors) ---
q = ax.quiver(
    LONc[mask_sig], LATc[mask_sig],
    U_mean[mask_sig], V_mean[mask_sig],
    scale=QUIVER_SCALE,
    scale_units=QUIVER_SCALE_UNITS,
    width=QUIVER_WIDTH,
    headwidth=QUIVER_HEADWIDTH,
    color="black", zorder=4
)

# Reference vector
ax.quiverkey(
    q, X=QUIVER_KEY_POS[0], Y=QUIVER_KEY_POS[1], U=QUIVER_REF_MS,
    label=f"{QUIVER_REF_MS:.1f} m s⁻¹", labelpos=QUIVER_KEY_LABELPOS,
    coordinates="axes"
)

# --- Title ---
plt.title(
    f"Rainy Cyclone UNIQUE-System {title_mode} + Mean Vectors ({(1-SIG_LEVEL)*100:.0f}% conf.)\n"
    f"(Genesis <{GENESIS_LAT_MAX}°N, TL≥{TRACK_LEN_MIN}, Speed ≥{SPEED_MIN_MS} m/s, "
    f"Q>{Q_RECORD_MIN}, Grid={GRID_SIZE}°, MinSamples={MIN_SAMPLES})"
)

# --- Save ---
plt.savefig("../FIGURES/track_density_with_sig_vectors.png", dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
plt.show()

import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature
from scipy.stats import ttest_1samp
import geopandas as gpd

# ============================================================
# USER-CONTROL PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
GRID_SIZE      = 2.0
LAT_RANGE      = (5, 40)
LON_RANGE      = (60, 105)

GENESIS_LAT_MAX = 25
TRACK_LEN_MIN   = 8
SPEED_MIN_MS    = 1
Q_RECORD_MIN    = 2.0
MIN_SAMPLES     = 10
SIG_LEVEL       = 0.1

DENSITY_MODE    = "mean"
DATA_FILE       = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
N_YEARS         = 2019 - 1998 + 1

QUIVER_SHOW_ONLY_SIGNIFICANT = True
QUIVER_REF_MS     = 2.0
QUIVER_REF_INCH   = 0.2
QUIVER_SCALE_UNITS = "inches"
QUIVER_SCALE      = QUIVER_REF_MS / QUIVER_REF_INCH
QUIVER_WIDTH      = 0.003
QUIVER_HEADWIDTH  = 4
QUIVER_KEY_POS    = (0.85, 1.02)
QUIVER_KEY_LABELPOS = 'E'

MIN_DIFF_POINTS = 12
FONT_SIZE = 12  # Publication font size

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)
track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values
lat_rec = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
q_rec   = ds["Q_RECORD"].values
diff_rec = ds["DIFF_RECORD"].values

# Define grid
lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)

# ============================================================
# Helper functions
# ============================================================
def haversine(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
    R = 6371.0
    lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2 = map(np.radians, [lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2])
    dlat = lat2 - lat1
    dlon = lon2 - lon1
    a = np.sin(dlat/2)**2 + np.cos(lat1)*np.cos(lat2)*np.sin(dlon/2)**2
    return R * 2 * np.arcsin(np.sqrt(a))

def process_tracks(diff_condition, min_diff):
    H_unique = np.zeros((lat_bins.size - 1, lon_bins.size - 1), dtype=int)
    U_list = [[[] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[1])] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[0])]
    V_list = [[[] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[1])] for _ in range(H_unique.shape[0])]
    valid_ids = []
    dt = 6*3600

    for i in range(track_lengths.shape[0]):
        tl = int(track_lengths[i])
        if tl < TRACK_LEN_MIN:
            continue
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        if not (np.isfinite(lats[0]) and np.isfinite(lons[0])):
            continue
        if lats[0] >= GENESIS_LAT_MAX:
            continue
        # Mean speed
        dist_km = np.nansum(haversine(lats[:-1], lons[:-1], lats[1:], lons[1:]))
        hours = max(tl-1,1)*6
        mean_speed_ms = (dist_km*1000)/(hours*3600)
        if mean_speed_ms < SPEED_MIN_MS:
            continue
        if np.nanmax(q_rec[i,:tl]) <= Q_RECORD_MIN:
            continue
        # DIFF_RECORD filter
        diff_vals = diff_rec[i,:tl]
        if diff_condition == 'gt' and np.sum(diff_vals > min_diff) < MIN_DIFF_POINTS:
            continue
        if diff_condition == 'lt' and np.sum(diff_vals < min_diff) < MIN_DIFF_POINTS:
            continue
        # Unique density
        li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins)-1
        lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins)-1
        mask = (li >=0) & (li<H_unique.shape[0]) & (lj>=0) & (lj<H_unique.shape[1])
        visited = set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask]))
        for ii,jj in visited:
            H_unique[ii,jj] += 1
        # Stepwise velocities
        for k in range(tl-1):
            if not (np.isfinite(lats[k]) and np.isfinite(lons[k]) and np.isfinite(lats[k+1]) and np.isfinite(lons[k+1])):
                continue
            ii = np.digitize(lats[k], lat_bins)-1
            jj = np.digitize(lons[k], lon_bins)-1
            if ii<0 or ii>=H_unique.shape[0] or jj<0 or jj>=H_unique.shape[1]:
                continue
            dlat = lats[k+1]-lats[k]
            dlon = lons[k+1]-lons[k]
            mean_lat_rad = np.radians((lats[k]+lats[k+1])/2.0)
            dy_m = dlat*111e3
            dx_m = dlon*111e3*np.cos(mean_lat_rad)
            u = dx_m/dt
            v = dy_m/dt
            U_list[ii][jj].append(u)
            V_list[ii][jj].append(v)
        valid_ids.append(i)

    # Density
    if DENSITY_MODE.lower() == 'mean':
        H_plot = H_unique / N_YEARS
    else:
        H_plot = H_unique

    # Mean vectors
    U_mean = np.full_like(H_unique, np.nan, dtype=float)
    V_mean = np.full_like(H_unique, np.nan, dtype=float)
    mask_sig = np.zeros_like(H_unique, dtype=bool)

    for ii in range(H_unique.shape[0]):
        for jj in range(H_unique.shape[1]):
            u_vals = np.asarray(U_list[ii][jj], dtype=float)
            v_vals = np.asarray(V_list[ii][jj], dtype=float)
            if u_vals.size < MIN_SAMPLES:
                continue
            t_u,p_u = ttest_1samp(u_vals,0.0,nan_policy='omit')
            t_v,p_v = ttest_1samp(v_vals,0.0,nan_policy='omit')
            if QUIVER_SHOW_ONLY_SIGNIFICANT:
                if (p_u<SIG_LEVEL) or (p_v<SIG_LEVEL):
                    U_mean[ii,jj]=np.nanmean(u_vals)
                    V_mean[ii,jj]=np.nanmean(v_vals)
                    mask_sig[ii,jj]=True
            else:
                U_mean[ii,jj]=np.nanmean(u_vals)
                V_mean[ii,jj]=np.nanmean(v_vals)
                mask_sig[ii,jj]=True

    return H_plot, U_mean, V_mean, mask_sig

# ============================================================
# Prepare figure with 2 subplots
# ============================================================
fig, axes = plt.subplots(1,2,figsize=(22,9), subplot_kw={'projection': ccrs.PlateCarree()})

# --- India shapefiles ---
country = gpd.read_file("/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/india-shapefile/India_Country_Boundary.shp").to_crs(epsg=4326)

    # Add gridlines with labels

import xarray as xr

# === Open NetCDF ===
ds = xr.open_dataset(
    "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
)
#print(ds)

# === Choose which cyclone/system to plot ===
system_index = 11198   # <-- change this number

# Extract track length
track_len = int(ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values[system_index])

# Extract system variables
lats = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values[system_index, :track_len]
lons = ds["LON_RECORD"].values[system_index, :track_len]
intensity = ds["VOM_RECORD"].values[system_index, :track_len]
times = ds["TIME_RECORD"].values[system_index, :track_len]

# === Convert TIME_RECORD robustly ===
def convert_time(times):
    """Convert TIME_RECORD to datetime, handling both YYYYMMDDHH and hours-since-1900."""
    times = np.array(times)

    # Case 1: looks like YYYYMMDDHH
    if np.nanmin(times) > 1e9 and np.nanmax(times) < 1e11:
        return [datetime.strptime(str(int(t)), "%Y%m%d%H") for t in times if not np.isnan(t)]

    # Case 2: hours since 1900-01-01
    base_time = pd.Timestamp("1900-01-01 00:00:00")
    mask = np.isfinite(times) & (times > -1e6) & (times < 1e6*24)  # only keep reasonable values
    return pd.to_datetime(times[mask], unit="h", origin=base_time).to_pydatetime().tolist()

times = convert_time(times)

# === Prepare LineCollection ===
points = np.array([lons, lats]).T.reshape(-1, 1, 2)
segments = np.concatenate([points[:-1], points[1:]], axis=1)

lc = LineCollection(
    segments,
    cmap="coolwarm",
    norm=plt.Normalize(np.nanmin(intensity), np.nanmax(intensity))
)
lc.set_array(intensity[:-1])
lc.set_linewidth(2.5)
lc.set_alpha(0.9)

# === Plot Map (focused on India) ===
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(9, 11))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.set_extent([68, 80, 15, 25], crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())  # India & neighborhood

ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=":")
ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor="lightyellow")
ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor="lightblue")
ax.add_feature(cfeature.STATES.with_scale("50m"), linewidth=0.5)

ax.add_collection(lc)

# Start & End markers
ax.plot(lons[0], lats[0], "o", color="green", markersize=8,
        transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label="Start")
ax.plot(lons[-1], lats[-1], "X", color="red", markersize=8,
        transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label="End")

# Add date labels every ~5 points (if times available)
if len(times) > 0:
    for i in range(0, min(len(lats), len(times)), 5):
        try:
            date_label = times[i].strftime("%d/%m")
            ax.text(lons[i]+0.25, lats[i]+0.25, date_label,
                    fontsize=8, transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),
                    rotation=25, color="black")
        except Exception:
            pass  # skip bad times

# Colorbar
cb = plt.colorbar(lc, ax=ax, orientation="horizontal", fraction=0.045, pad=0.05)
cb.set_label("Vorticity Intensity (10⁻⁵ s⁻¹)", fontsize=10)
cb.ax.tick_params(labelsize=9)

plt.title(f"MTC Track (System {times[0]})", fontsize=14, fontweight="bold")

Example 2: Track of a random low-pressure system (LPS) that formed in the Bay of Bengal and reached the Arabian Sea, precisely tracked by the tracking algorithm.

The accuracy of the method is demonstrated below for Cyclone Index = 27716. The tracking algorithm captured a track length of 51 six-hourly time steps, starting on 2016-08-13 18:00 UTC and ending on 2016-08-26 06:00 UTC, as recorded in the TIME_RECORD variable of the tracking algorithm output file.

Cyclone Track Density Analysis with Stationary Cyclone Filtering¶

This Python script calculates and visualizes unique-system cyclone density from ERA5-derived mid-tropospheric (600 hPa) cyclone tracks. Key steps and logic are as follows:

  1. User Parameters

    • GRID_SIZE, LAT_RANGE, LON_RANGE: Define the spatial resolution and extent for the density grid.
    • GENESIS_LAT_MAX, TRACK_LEN_MIN, SPEED_MIN_MS, Q_RECORD_MIN: Filter cyclones by genesis latitude, minimum track length, mean speed, and mid-level humidity.
    • SPEED_STATIONARY_THRESHOLD, MIN_STATIONARY_POINTS: Cyclones that remain nearly stationary for a minimum number of consecutive steps are excluded.
    • DENSITY_MODE: Option to compute mean density per year or total density over all years.

  2. Data Loading

    • The script reads a NetCDF file containing cyclone tracks at 600 hPa, extracting latitude, longitude, track length, and humidity (Q_RECORD).

  3. Cyclone Filtering

    • Tracks shorter than TRACK_LEN_MIN or with genesis beyond GENESIS_LAT_MAX are discarded.
    • Mean speed is computed using stepwise distances between consecutive track points. Tracks with mean speed below SPEED_MIN_MS or maximum Q below Q_RECORD_MIN are filtered out.
    • Stationary cyclone check: Tracks with consecutive points moving slower than SPEED_STATIONARY_THRESHOLD for at least MIN_STATIONARY_POINTS are removed.

  4. Density Grid Calculation

    • The domain is divided into latitude-longitude bins, and unique cyclone visits per grid cell are counted.
    • If DENSITY_MODE="mean", the count is normalized by the number of years (N_YEARS).

  5. Visualization

    • The density field is plotted using Cartopy with coastlines, borders, land, and ocean.
    • A color map (Reds) represents the unique-system density.
    • The resulting figure highlights regions with frequent cyclone activity while excluding stationary or weak systems.

  6. Output

    • A high-resolution PNG file is saved for publication-quality figures.

import numpy as np
import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature

# ============================================================
# USER-CONTROL PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
GRID_SIZE = 2.0         # degrees
LAT_RANGE = (5, 32)
LON_RANGE = (60, 105)

GENESIS_LAT_MAX = 45
TRACK_LEN_MIN   = 12
SPEED_MIN_MS    = 5.0
Q_RECORD_MIN    = 1.0

# Stationary cyclone filter
SPEED_STATIONARY_THRESHOLD = 1   # m/s
MIN_STATIONARY_POINTS      = 2           # minimum consecutive points below threshold

DENSITY_MODE = "mean"
DATA_FILE    = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
N_YEARS      = 2019 - 1998 + 1

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)

def haversine(lat1, lon1, lat2, lon2):
    R=6371.0
    lat1,lon1,lat2,lon2 = map(np.radians,[lat1,lon1,lat2,lon2])
    dlat=lat2-lat1; dlon=lon2-lon1
    a=np.sin(dlat/2)**2+np.cos(lat1)*np.cos(lat2)*np.sin(dlon/2)**2
    return R*2*np.arcsin(np.sqrt(a))

# Extract
track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values
lat_rec       = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec       = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
q_rec         = ds["Q_RECORD"].values

# Define grid
lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]+GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1]+GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
H_unique = np.zeros((lat_bins.size-1, lon_bins.size-1), dtype=int)

valid_ids = []

dt = 6*3600  # seconds (6h timestep)

for i in range(track_lengths.shape[0]):
    tl = int(track_lengths[i])
    if tl < TRACK_LEN_MIN: 
        continue
    
    lats = lat_rec[i,:tl]; lons = lon_rec[i,:tl]
    if not (np.isfinite(lats[0]) and np.isfinite(lons[0])): 
        continue
    if lats[0] >= GENESIS_LAT_MAX: 
        continue
    
    # compute stepwise speed
    dy = np.diff(lats)*111e3
    dx = np.diff(lons)*111e3*np.cos(np.radians((lats[:-1]+lats[1:])/2))
    speed = np.sqrt(dx**2 + dy**2)/dt
    
    # filter mean speed
    mean_speed_ms = np.nanmean(speed)
    if mean_speed_ms < SPEED_MIN_MS: 
        continue
        
    if np.nanmax(q_rec[i,:tl]) <= Q_RECORD_MIN:
        continue
    
    # filter stationary cyclones
    stationary = speed < SPEED_STATIONARY_THRESHOLD
    # check for consecutive stationary points
    count = 0
    stationary_flag = False
    for s in stationary:
        if s:
            count += 1
            if count >= MIN_STATIONARY_POINTS:
                stationary_flag = True
                break
        else:
            count = 0
    if stationary_flag:
        continue
    
    # unique visit
    li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins)-1
    lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins)-1
    mask = (li>=0)&(li<H_unique.shape[0])&(lj>=0)&(lj<H_unique.shape[1])
    visited = set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask]))
    for (ii,jj) in visited:
        H_unique[ii,jj] += 1
    
    valid_ids.append(i)

print(f"Counted {len(valid_ids)} systems after stationary cyclone filtering.")

# ============================================================
# Density Mode
# ============================================================
if DENSITY_MODE.lower() == "mean":
    H_plot = H_unique / N_YEARS
    cbar_label = "Mean unique-system density (#/yr per grid cell)"
    title_mode = "Mean Density per Year"
else:
    H_plot = H_unique
    cbar_label = "Unique-system density (total # per grid cell)"
    title_mode = "Total Density (1998–2019)"

# ============================================================
# Plot
# ============================================================
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
ax = plt.axes(projection=ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]], crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())
ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=1)
ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=":")
ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor="lightyellow")
ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor="lightblue")

LON, LAT = np.meshgrid(lon_bins, lat_bins)
m = ax.pcolormesh(LON, LAT, H_plot, cmap="Reds", shading="auto")
cb = plt.colorbar(m, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04)
cb.set_label(cbar_label)
plt.title(f"Rainy Cyclone UNIQUE-System {title_mode}\n"
          f"(Genesis <{GENESIS_LAT_MAX}°N, TL≥{TRACK_LEN_MIN}, Speed ≥{SPEED_MIN_MS} m/s, "
          f"Q>{Q_RECORD_MIN}, Stationary filtered, Grid={GRID_SIZE}°)")
plt.savefig("../FIGURES/track_density_unique_stationary_filtered.png", dpi=300, bbox_inches="tight")
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import xarray as xr
impmort matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature

# ============================================================
# USER PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
GRID_SIZE = 3.0
LAT_RANGE = (5, 32)
LON_RANGE = (60, 105)
MIN_TRACK_POINTS = 12
MIN_COEXIST_POINTS = 4   # time overlap points required
MIN_BOB_STEPS = 4        # BoB presence required

# Boxes
AS_LAT_RANGE  = (18, 22)
AS_LON_RANGE  = (65, 74)
BoB_LAT_RANGE = (13, 40)
BoB_LON_RANGE = (75, 95)

DATA_FILE = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
N_YEARS = 2019 - 1998 + 1

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)

track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values.astype(int)
lat_rec = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
time_rec = ds["TIME_RECORD"].values

lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)

# ============================================================
# Helpers
# ============================================================
def in_BoB(lat, lon):
    return (BoB_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat <= BoB_LAT_RANGE[1]) and \
           (BoB_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon <= BoB_LON_RANGE[1])

def reaches_AS(i):
    """Track i ever enters Arabian Sea box (≤74E & 17–22N)."""
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
    lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
    return np.any((lons <= AS_LON_RANGE[1]) &
                  (AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lats) & (lats <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1]))

def time_coexist(as_idx, bob_idx):
    """AS and BoB overlap in time by >= MIN_COEXIST_POINTS."""
    tl_as = track_lengths[as_idx]
    tl_bob = track_lengths[bob_idx]
    as_times = time_rec[as_idx, :tl_as]
    bob_times = time_rec[bob_idx, :tl_bob]
    common = np.intersect1d(as_times, bob_times)
    return common.size >= MIN_COEXIST_POINTS

def compute_density(track_ids):
    H = np.zeros((lat_bins.size - 1, lon_bins.size - 1), dtype=int)
    for i in track_ids:
        tl = track_lengths[i]
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins) - 1
        lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins) - 1
        mask = (li >= 0) & (li < H.shape[0]) & (lj >= 0) & (lj < H.shape[1])
        for (ii, jj) in set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask])):
            H[ii, jj] += 1
    return H

# ============================================================
# Identify genesis systems
# ============================================================
AS_ids, BoB_ids = [], []

ntracks = track_lengths.shape[0]
for i in range(ntracks):
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    if tl < MIN_TRACK_POINTS:
        continue
    lat0, lon0 = lat_rec[i, 0], lon_rec[i, 0]
    if not np.isfinite(lat0) or not np.isfinite(lon0):
        continue

    if AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat0 <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1] and AS_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon0 <= AS_LON_RANGE[1]:
        AS_ids.append(i)

    if in_BoB(lat0, lon0):
        # require ≥8 BoB points
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        n_bob = np.sum([(in_BoB(la, lo)) for la, lo in zip(lats, lons)])
        if n_bob >= MIN_BOB_STEPS:
            BoB_ids.append(i)

# ============================================================
# Panel (a): BoB genesis (≥75E) that reach Arabian Sea
# ============================================================
A_ids = [i for i in BoB_ids if reaches_AS(i)]

# ============================================================
# Panels (b–d): AS genesis split by BoB coexistence timing
# ============================================================
B_ids, C_ids, D_ids = [], [], []
for i in AS_ids:
    coex_after, coex_before = False, False
    for j in BoB_ids:
        if time_coexist(i, j):
            if time_rec[i, 0] > time_rec[j, 0]:
                coex_after = True
            else:
                coex_before = True
    if coex_after:
        B_ids.append(i)
    elif coex_before:
        C_ids.append(i)
    else:
        D_ids.append(i)

print("Counts:")
print("BoB genesis → reaches AS (panel a):", len(A_ids))
print("AS after BoB coexistence (panel b):", len(B_ids))
print("AS before BoB coexistence (panel c):", len(C_ids))
print("AS with no BoB coexistence (panel d):", len(D_ids))

# ============================================================
# Compute densities
# ============================================================
densities = [compute_density(A_ids), compute_density(B_ids),
             compute_density(C_ids), compute_density(D_ids)]

# ============================================================
# Mean track function (final version)
# ============================================================
def compute_mean_track(track_ids):
    """Mean track (lat, lon) start-aligned, extended to longest track,
       NaN-aware mean."""
    if len(track_ids) == 0:
        return None, None

    max_len = max(int(track_lengths[i]) for i in track_ids)
    lat_stack = np.full((len(track_ids), max_len), np.nan)
    lon_stack = np.full((len(track_ids), max_len), np.nan)

    kept = 0
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = int(track_lengths[idx])
        lats = np.array(lat_rec[idx, :tl], dtype=float)
        lons = np.array(lon_rec[idx, :tl], dtype=float)
        lats[~np.isfinite(lats)] = np.nan
        lons[~np.isfinite(lons)] = np.nan
        if np.all(np.isnan(lats)) or np.all(np.isnan(lons)):
            continue
        lat_stack[kept, :tl] = lats
        lon_stack[kept, :tl] = lons
        # extend with last valid point
        if tl < max_len:
            last_lat = lats[~np.isnan(lats)][-1]
            last_lon = lons[~np.isnan(lons)][-1]
            lat_stack[kept, tl:max_len] = last_lat
            lon_stack[kept, tl:max_len] = last_lon
        kept += 1

    if kept == 0:
        return None, None

    lat_stack = lat_stack[:kept]
    lon_stack = lon_stack[:kept]
    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)

mean_tracks = [
    compute_mean_track(A_ids),
    compute_mean_track(B_ids),
    compute_mean_track(C_ids),
    compute_mean_track(D_ids)
]

# ============================================================
# Plot with mean tracks
# ============================================================
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12),
                         subplot_kw={'projection': ccrs.PlateCarree()})
titles = ['(a) BoB genesis (≥75E) that reach Arabian Sea (≤74E, 17–22N)',
          '(b) AS genesis after BoB coexisted',
          '(c) AS genesis before BoB coexisted',
          '(d) AS genesis with no BoB coexistence']
colors = ["blue", "green", "purple", "black"]

for ax, density, title, mean_pair, col in zip(axes.flatten(), densities, titles, mean_tracks, colors):
    ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]])
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor='lightyellow')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor='lightblue')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=0.7)
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=':', linewidth=0.5)

    LON, LAT = np.meshgrid(lon_bins, lat_bins)
    m = ax.pcolormesh(LON, LAT, density / N_YEARS, cmap='Reds', shading='auto')
    plt.colorbar(m, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04, label='Mean #/yr per grid cell')

    if mean_pair is not None:
        mlat, mlon = mean_pair
        ax.plot(mlon, mlat, color=col, linewidth=2.5, marker="o", markersize=3,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label="Mean track")
        ax.plot(mlon[0], mlat[0], marker="*", markersize=9, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.plot(mlon[-1], mlat[-1], marker="X", markersize=7, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=9)

    ax.set_title(title)

plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.25, wspace=0.15)
plt.savefig("../FIGURES/conditional_AS_track_density_time_overlap_mean_tracks.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

import numpy as np
import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature
from scipy.interpolate import interp1d

# ============================================================
# USER PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
GRID_SIZE = 4.0
LAT_RANGE = (5, 32)
LON_RANGE = (60, 105)

MIN_TRACK_POINTS = 12     # minimum steps to consider a track
MIN_COEXIST_POINTS = 4    # time overlap points required
MIN_BOB_STEPS = 4         # BoB presence required during lifecycle

# Intensity thresholds (now user-controlled!)
MIN_VORTICITY = 0.0       # mean vorticity threshold
MAX_VORTICITY = None      # if set (e.g. 1.5e-4), filters out too-strong systems
MIN_MOISTURE = 2.0        # global minimum moisture
MIN_AS_MOISTURE = 4.0     # stronger requirement for AS tracks

# Boxes
AS_LAT_RANGE  = (18, 25)
AS_LON_RANGE  = (65, 74)
BoB_LAT_RANGE = (15, 25)
BoB_LON_RANGE = (75, 95)

DATA_FILE = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
N_YEARS = 2019 - 1998 + 1

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)

track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values.astype(int)
lat_rec = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
time_rec = ds["TIME_RECORD"].values
VOM_rec = ds["VOM_RECORD"].values  # vorticity/intensity
Q_REC = ds["Q_RECORD"].values      # moisture (specific humidity)

lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)

# ============================================================
# Helpers
# ============================================================
def in_AS(lat, lon):
    return (AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1]) and \
           (AS_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon <= AS_LON_RANGE[1])

def reaches_AS_from_BoB(i):
    """BoB track i ever enters Arabian Sea box."""
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
    lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
    return np.any((AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lats) & (lats <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1]) &
                  (lons <= AS_LON_RANGE[1]) & (lons >= AS_LON_RANGE[0]))

def time_coexist(as_idx, bob_idx):
    """AS and BoB overlap in time by >= MIN_COEXIST_POINTS."""
    tl_as = track_lengths[as_idx]
    tl_bob = track_lengths[bob_idx]
    as_times = time_rec[as_idx, :tl_as]
    bob_times = time_rec[bob_idx, :tl_bob]
    common = np.intersect1d(as_times, bob_times)
    return common.size >= MIN_COEXIST_POINTS

def compute_density(track_ids):
    H = np.zeros((lat_bins.size - 1, lon_bins.size - 1), dtype=int)
    for i in track_ids:
        tl = track_lengths[i]
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins) - 1
        lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins) - 1
        mask = (li >= 0) & (li < H.shape[0]) & (lj >= 0) & (lj < H.shape[1])
        for (ii, jj) in set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask])):
            H[ii, jj] += 1
    return H

# ============================================================
# Identify genesis systems with global moisture + vorticity criteria
# ============================================================
AS_ids, BoB_ids = [], []
ntracks = track_lengths.shape[0]

for i in range(ntracks):
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    if tl < MIN_TRACK_POINTS:
        continue

    lat0, lon0 = lat_rec[i, 0], lon_rec[i, 0]
    if not np.isfinite(lat0) or not np.isfinite(lon0):
        continue

    mean_vort = np.nanmean(VOM_rec[i, :tl])
    mean_moist = np.nanmean(Q_REC[i, :tl])

    # Apply thresholds
    if mean_moist <= MIN_MOISTURE:
        continue
    if mean_vort < MIN_VORTICITY:
        continue
    if MAX_VORTICITY is not None and mean_vort > MAX_VORTICITY:
        continue

    # Collect AS genesis tracks
    if in_AS(lat0, lon0):
        AS_ids.append(i)

    # Collect BoB genesis tracks
    if (BoB_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat0 < 25) and (BoB_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon0 <= BoB_LON_RANGE[1]):
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        in_bob_points = [(BoB_LAT_RANGE[0] <= la <= BoB_LAT_RANGE[1]) and
                         (BoB_LON_RANGE[0] <= lo <= BoB_LON_RANGE[1])
                         for la, lo in zip(lats, lons)]
        if np.sum(in_bob_points) >= MIN_BOB_STEPS:
            BoB_ids.append(i)

# ============================================================
# Partition BoB tracks into A, B, C
# ============================================================
A_ids, B_ids, C_ids = [], [], []
remaining_BoB = set(BoB_ids)

# 1. BoB tracks that reach AS
for i in list(remaining_BoB):
    if reaches_AS_from_BoB(i):
        A_ids.append(i)
        remaining_BoB.remove(i)

# 2. BoB tracks coexisting with AS (strong AS only)
for i in list(remaining_BoB):
    coex = False
    for j in AS_ids:
        mean_vort_j = np.nanmean(VOM_rec[j, :track_lengths[j]])
        mean_moist_j = np.nanmean(Q_REC[j, :track_lengths[j]])
        if mean_vort_j > MIN_VORTICITY and mean_moist_j > MIN_AS_MOISTURE and time_coexist(j, i):
            coex = True
            break
    if coex:
        B_ids.append(i)
        remaining_BoB.remove(i)

# 3. Remaining BoB
C_ids = list(remaining_BoB)

print("Counts:")
print("BoB genesis → reaches AS (panel a):", len(A_ids))
print("BoB genesis coexisting with AS (panel b):", len(B_ids))
print("BoB genesis without AS coexistence (panel c):", len(C_ids))

# ============================================================
# Compute densities
# ============================================================
densities = [compute_density(A_ids), compute_density(B_ids), compute_density(C_ids)]

# ============================================================
# Mean track function (normalized lifetime)
# ============================================================
def compute_mean_track_normalized(track_ids, N_norm=60):
    if len(track_ids) == 0:
        return None, None

    lat_stack, lon_stack = [], []
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = int(track_lengths[idx])
        if tl < 16:
            continue

        lats = lat_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        lons = lon_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        if np.all(~np.isfinite(lats)) or np.all(~np.isfinite(lons)):
            continue

        frac = np.linspace(0, 1, tl)
        f_lat = interp1d(frac, lats, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        f_lon = interp1d(frac, lons, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        new_frac = np.linspace(0, 1, N_norm)

        lat_stack.append(f_lat(new_frac))
        lon_stack.append(f_lon(new_frac))

    if len(lat_stack) == 0:
        return None, None

    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)

# ============================================================
# Compute mean tracks
# ============================================================
mean_tracks = [
    compute_mean_track_normalized(A_ids),
    compute_mean_track_normalized(B_ids),
    compute_mean_track_normalized(C_ids),
]
# ============================================================
# Plot with mean tracks (a–d) in 2x2 format
# ============================================================
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12),
                         subplot_kw={'projection': ccrs.PlateCarree()})
axes = axes.flatten()  # make it easier to index

titles = [
    '(a) BoB tracks reaching AS',
    '(b) BoB tracks coexisting with AS (vort & moisture)',
    '(c) BoB tracks without AS coexistence',
    '(d) Normalized mean tracks (lifetime-scaled)'
]
colors = ["blue", "green", "black"]

# ------------------------
# Panels (a)–(c): densities + mean track
# ------------------------
for ax, density, title, mean_pair, col in zip(axes[:3], densities, titles[:3], mean_tracks, colors):
    ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]])
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor='lightyellow')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor='lightblue')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=0.7)
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=':', linewidth=0.5)

    LON, LAT = np.meshgrid(lon_bins, lat_bins)
    m = ax.pcolormesh(LON, LAT, density / N_YEARS, cmap='Reds', shading='auto')
    plt.colorbar(m, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04, label='Mean #/yr per grid cell')

    if mean_pair is not None:
        mlat, mlon = mean_pair
        ax.plot(mlon, mlat, color=col, linewidth=2.5, marker="o", markersize=3,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label="Mean track")
        ax.plot(mlon[0], mlat[0], marker="*", markersize=9, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.plot(mlon[-1], mlat[-1], marker="X", markersize=7, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=9)

    ax.set_title(title)

# ------------------------
# Panel (d): overlay normalized mean tracks
# ------------------------
ax = axes[3]
ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]])
ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor='lightyellow')
ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor='lightblue')
ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=0.7)
ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=':', linewidth=0.5)
ax.set_title(titles[3])

all_norm_tracks = [
    compute_mean_track_normalized(A_ids),
    compute_mean_track_normalized(B_ids),
    compute_mean_track_normalized(C_ids),
]

for (mlat, mlon), col, lab in zip(all_norm_tracks, colors, ['A: reach AS', 'B: coexist', 'C: no coexist']):
    if mlat is not None:
        ax.plot(mlon, mlat, color=col, linewidth=2.5, marker="o", markersize=3,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label=lab)
        ax.plot(mlon[0], mlat[0], marker="*", markersize=9, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.plot(mlon[-1], mlat[-1], marker="X", markersize=7, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())

ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=9)

# ------------------------
# Final adjustments
# ------------------------
plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=0.25, wspace=0.15)
plt.savefig("../FIGURES/BoB_track_density_AS_conditioned_vort_moisture_2x2.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()

# ============================================================
# Mean track function (normalized lifetime)
# ============================================================
def compute_mean_track_normalized(track_ids, N_norm=10):
    if len(track_ids) == 0:
        return None, None

    lat_stack, lon_stack = [], []
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = int(track_lengths[idx])
        if tl < 16:
            continue

        lats = lat_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        lons = lon_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        if np.all(~np.isfinite(lats)) or np.all(~np.isfinite(lons)):
            continue

        frac = np.linspace(0, 1, tl)
        f_lat = interp1d(frac, lats, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        f_lon = interp1d(frac, lons, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        new_frac = np.linspace(0, 1, N_norm)

        lat_stack.append(f_lat(new_frac))
        lon_stack.append(f_lon(new_frac))

    if len(lat_stack) == 0:
        return None, None

    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)


# ============================================================
# Mean track function (padded, genesis-aligned)
# ============================================================
def compute_mean_track_padded(track_ids):
    if len(track_ids) == 0:
        return None, None

    max_len = max(track_lengths[i] for i in track_ids if track_lengths[i] >= 16)
    lat_stack, lon_stack = [], []
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = int(track_lengths[idx])
        if tl < 16:
            continue

        lats = lat_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        lons = lon_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        if np.all(~np.isfinite(lats)) or np.all(~np.isfinite(lons)):
            continue

        # pad with last value to max_len
        if tl < max_len:
            lats = np.pad(lats, (0, max_len - tl), constant_values=lats[-1])
            lons = np.pad(lons, (0, max_len - tl), constant_values=lons[-1])

        lat_stack.append(lats)
        lon_stack.append(lons)

    if len(lat_stack) == 0:
        return None, None

    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)

import numpy as np
import xarray as xr
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import cartopy.crs as ccrs
import cartopy.feature as cfeature
from cartopy.mpl.ticker import LongitudeFormatter, LatitudeFormatter
from scipy.interpolate import interp1d
import os

# ============================================================
# USER PARAMETERS
# ============================================================
DATA_FILE = "/home/pradeep/Desktop/AUTOMATIC_TRACKING_GUTHUB/DATA/MID_CYCLONE_TRACKS_JUN_SEP_1998-2019_600hPa.nc"
OUTDIR = "../FIGURES"

GRID_SIZE = 2.0
LAT_RANGE = (5, 32)
LON_RANGE = (60, 105)

N_YEARS = 2019 - 1998 + 1

# Genesis filtering
MIN_TRACK_POINTS = 12
MIN_COEXIST_POINTS = 4
MIN_BOB_STEPS = 4

# Intensity thresholds
MIN_VORTICITY = 0.0
MAX_VORTICITY = None
MIN_MOISTURE = 1.0
MIN_AS_MOISTURE = 1.0

# Boxes
AS_LAT_RANGE  = (18, 25)
AS_LON_RANGE  = (65, 74)
BoB_LAT_RANGE = (15, 27)
BoB_LON_RANGE = (75, 95)

# Mean track method: "normalized" or "padded"
MEAN_METHOD = "padded"

# ============================================================
# Load dataset
# ============================================================
ds = xr.open_dataset(DATA_FILE)

track_lengths = ds["TRACK_LENGTH"].values.astype(int)
lat_rec = ds["LAT_RECORD"].values
lon_rec = ds["LON_RECORD"].values
time_rec = ds["TIME_RECORD"].values
VOM_rec = ds["VOM_RECORD"].values
Q_REC = ds["Q_RECORD"].values

lat_bins = np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)
lon_bins = np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + GRID_SIZE, GRID_SIZE)

# ============================================================
# Helpers
# ============================================================
def in_AS(lat, lon):
    """Check if a point is in AS box."""
    return (AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1]) and \
           (AS_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon <= AS_LON_RANGE[1])

def reaches_AS_from_BoB(i):
    """Check if BoB track later enters AS box."""
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
    lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
    return np.any((AS_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lats) & (lats <= AS_LAT_RANGE[1]) &
                  (AS_LON_RANGE[0] <= lons) & (lons <= AS_LON_RANGE[1]))

def time_coexist(as_idx, bob_idx):
    """Check if AS & BoB tracks overlap for ≥ MIN_COEXIST_POINTS timesteps."""
    tl_as = track_lengths[as_idx]
    tl_bob = track_lengths[bob_idx]
    as_times = np.round(time_rec[as_idx, :tl_as].astype(float), 3)
    bob_times = np.round(time_rec[bob_idx, :tl_bob].astype(float), 3)
    return np.intersect1d(as_times, bob_times).size >= MIN_COEXIST_POINTS

def compute_density(track_ids):
    """Grid-based track density count."""
    H = np.zeros((lat_bins.size - 1, lon_bins.size - 1), dtype=int)
    for i in track_ids:
        tl = track_lengths[i]
        lats = lat_rec[i, :tl]
        lons = lon_rec[i, :tl]
        li = np.digitize(lats, lat_bins) - 1
        lj = np.digitize(lons, lon_bins) - 1
        mask = (li >= 0) & (li < H.shape[0]) & (lj >= 0) & (lj < H.shape[1])
        for (ii, jj) in set(zip(li[mask], lj[mask])):
            H[ii, jj] += 1
    return H

# ============================================================
# Mean track functions
# ============================================================
def compute_mean_track_normalized(track_ids, N_norm=10):
    """Resample tracks to common fractional length [0–1]."""
    lat_stack, lon_stack = [], []
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = track_lengths[idx]
        if tl < 16:
            continue
        lats = lat_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        lons = lon_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        if not np.any(np.isfinite(lats)):
            continue
        frac = np.linspace(0, 1, tl)
        f_lat = interp1d(frac, lats, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        f_lon = interp1d(frac, lons, kind="linear", fill_value="extrapolate")
        new_frac = np.linspace(0, 1, N_norm)
        lat_stack.append(f_lat(new_frac))
        lon_stack.append(f_lon(new_frac))
    if len(lat_stack) == 0:
        return None, None
    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)

def compute_mean_track_padded(track_ids):
    """Pad tracks to common max length, then average."""
    valid_lengths = [track_lengths[i] for i in track_ids if track_lengths[i] >= 4]
    if len(valid_lengths) == 0:
        return None, None
    max_len = max(valid_lengths)
    lat_stack, lon_stack = [], []
    for idx in track_ids:
        tl = track_lengths[idx]
        if tl < 16:
            continue
        lats = lat_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        lons = lon_rec[idx, :tl].astype(float)
        if not np.any(np.isfinite(lats)):
            continue
        if tl < max_len:
            lats = np.pad(lats, (0, max_len - tl), constant_values=lats[-1])
            lons = np.pad(lons, (0, max_len - tl), constant_values=lons[-1])
        lat_stack.append(lats)
        lon_stack.append(lons)
    return np.nanmean(lat_stack, axis=0), np.nanmean(lon_stack, axis=0)

def get_mean_track(track_ids):
    """Choose mean track method globally."""
    if MEAN_METHOD == "normalized":
        return compute_mean_track_normalized(track_ids)
    elif MEAN_METHOD == "padded":
        return compute_mean_track_padded(track_ids)
    else:
        raise ValueError("Invalid MEAN_METHOD")

# ============================================================
# Identify AS & BoB genesis tracks
# ============================================================
AS_ids, BoB_ids = [], []
ntracks = track_lengths.shape[0]

for i in range(ntracks):
    tl = track_lengths[i]
    if tl < MIN_TRACK_POINTS:
        continue

    lat0, lon0 = lat_rec[i, 0], lon_rec[i, 0]
    if not np.isfinite(lat0) or not np.isfinite(lon0):
        continue

    mean_vort = np.nanmean(VOM_rec[i, :tl])
    mean_moist = np.nanmean(Q_REC[i, :tl])
    if mean_moist <= MIN_MOISTURE or mean_vort < MIN_VORTICITY:
        continue
    if MAX_VORTICITY is not None and mean_vort > MAX_VORTICITY:
        continue

    if in_AS(lat0, lon0):
        AS_ids.append(i)

    if (BoB_LAT_RANGE[0] <= lat0 <= BoB_LAT_RANGE[1]) and \
       (BoB_LON_RANGE[0] <= lon0 <= BoB_LON_RANGE[1]):
        in_bob_points = [(BoB_LAT_RANGE[0] <= la <= BoB_LAT_RANGE[1]) and
                         (BoB_LON_RANGE[0] <= lo <= BoB_LON_RANGE[1])
                         for la, lo in zip(lat_rec[i, :tl], lon_rec[i, :tl])]
        if np.sum(in_bob_points) >= MIN_BOB_STEPS:
            BoB_ids.append(i)

# ============================================================
# Partition BoB tracks: A, B, C
# ============================================================
A_ids, B_ids, C_ids = [], [], []
remaining_BoB = set(BoB_ids)

# Panel A: BoB → reaches AS
for i in list(remaining_BoB):
    if reaches_AS_from_BoB(i):
        A_ids.append(i)
        remaining_BoB.remove(i)

# Panel B: BoB coexisting with AS
for i in list(remaining_BoB):
    coex = False
    for j in AS_ids:
        mean_vort_j = np.nanmean(VOM_rec[j, :track_lengths[j]])
        mean_moist_j = np.nanmean(Q_REC[j, :track_lengths[j]])
        if mean_vort_j > MIN_VORTICITY and mean_moist_j > MIN_AS_MOISTURE and time_coexist(j, i):
            coex = True
            break
    if coex:
        B_ids.append(i)
        remaining_BoB.remove(i)

# Panel C: residual BoB tracks
C_ids = list(remaining_BoB)

print("Counts:")
print("BoB genesis → reaches AS (panel a):", len(A_ids))
print("BoB genesis coexisting with AS (panel b):", len(B_ids))
print("BoB genesis without AS coexistence (panel c):", len(C_ids))

# ============================================================
# Compute densities + mean tracks
# ============================================================
densities = [compute_density(A_ids), compute_density(B_ids), compute_density(C_ids)]
vmax = max(np.max(d) for d in densities) / N_YEARS

mean_tracks = [get_mean_track(A_ids),
               get_mean_track(B_ids),
               get_mean_track(C_ids)]

# ============================================================
# Plot (2×2 panels)
# ============================================================
fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(16, 12),
                         subplot_kw={'projection': ccrs.PlateCarree()})
axes = axes.flatten()

titles = [
    '(a) BoB tracks reaching AS',
    '(b) BoB tracks coexisting with AS (vort & moisture)',
    '(c) BoB tracks without AS coexistence',
    f'(d) Mean tracks ({MEAN_METHOD})'
]
colors = ["blue", "green", "black"]
def setup_map(ax, title):
    ax.set_extent([LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1], LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1]])
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.LAND, facecolor='lightyellow')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.OCEAN, facecolor='lightblue')
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.COASTLINE, linewidth=0.7)
    ax.add_feature(cfeature.BORDERS, linestyle=':', linewidth=0.5)
    ax.set_title(title)

    # Gridlines (NO labels here)
    ax.gridlines(draw_labels=False, linewidth=0.5,
                 color='gray', alpha=0.5, linestyle='--')

    # Now force ticks with Matplotlib
    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(LON_RANGE[0], LON_RANGE[1] + 1, 5),
                  crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())
    ax.set_yticks(np.arange(LAT_RANGE[0], LAT_RANGE[1] + 1, 5),
                  crs=ccrs.PlateCarree())

    # Format labels cleanly
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(LongitudeFormatter(zero_direction_label=True))
    ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(LatitudeFormatter())

    # Control font size & orientation
    for label in ax.get_xticklabels():
        label.set(rotation=0, ha="center", fontsize=9)
    for label in ax.get_yticklabels():
        label.set(rotation=0, va="center", fontsize=9)



# Panels (a–c): density + mean track
for ax, density, title, mean_pair, col in zip(axes[:3], densities, titles[:3], mean_tracks, colors):
    setup_map(ax, title)

    LON, LAT = np.meshgrid(lon_bins, lat_bins)
    m = ax.pcolormesh(LON, LAT, density / N_YEARS, cmap='Reds',
                      shading='auto', vmin=0, vmax=vmax)
    plt.colorbar(m, ax=ax, fraction=0.046, pad=0.04,
                 label='Mean #/yr per grid cell')

    if mean_pair is not None:
        mlat, mlon = mean_pair
        ax.plot(mlon, mlat, color=col, linewidth=2.5, marker="o", markersize=3,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label="Mean track")
        ax.plot(mlon[0], mlat[0], marker="*", markersize=9, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.plot(mlon[-1], mlat[-1], marker="X", markersize=7, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        leg = ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=9)
        leg.get_frame().set_alpha(0.6)

# Panel (d): compare normalized mean tracks (independent of MEAN_METHOD)
ax = axes[3]
setup_map(ax, titles[3])

for (mlat, mlon), col, lab in zip(
    [compute_mean_track_normalized(A_ids),
     compute_mean_track_normalized(B_ids),
     compute_mean_track_normalized(C_ids)],
    colors,
    ['A: reach AS', 'B: coexist', 'C: no coexist']):
    if mlat is not None:
        ax.plot(mlon, mlat, color=col, linewidth=2.5, marker="o", markersize=3,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), label=lab)
        ax.plot(mlon[0], mlat[0], marker="*", markersize=9, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())
        ax.plot(mlon[-1], mlat[-1], marker="X", markersize=7, color=col,
                transform=ccrs.PlateCarree())

leg = ax.legend(loc="upper right", fontsize=9)
leg.get_frame().set_alpha(0.6)

# Save
plt.tight_layout()
os.makedirs(OUTDIR, exist_ok=True)
plt.savefig(f"{OUTDIR}/BoB_track_density_AS_conditioned_vort_moisture_{MEAN_METHOD}_2x2.png", dpi=300)
plt.show()
